            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [  ¶  ¶ ( ¶ Anabasis Ammodendron ¶ ). ¶ Baron von Mueller has forwarded a packet of the seed of this plant with a view to its being tried in the Mildura district. ¶ The remaining text is a slight m...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.09.00h</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Mildura Cultivator</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Our experiment column: New forage plant',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mildura cultivator</seg>, 13 September, p. [3].</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[ <space unit="chars" quantity="21"/>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Anabasis Ammodendron</seg>).</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Baron von Mueller has forwarded a packet of the seed of this plant with a view to its being tried in the Mildura district.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The remaining text is a slight modification of the entry in B88.12.01, and may have been added by the editor.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Its natural habitat ranges from the Ural to Persia and Turkestan. It is the only arborescent plant in the drift sand deserts of those regions, and has been strongly recommended for naturalisation in other sandy or saline arid tracts. It is of the family of the Chenopads [i.e. Chenopods], or spinach, and attains a height of 20 feet. It endures a soil temperature of half the heat of boiling water, and in appearance resembles somewhat our lignum scrub. The young growths are tender and nutritious for stock, but the matured wood is hard and dense.]</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Anabasis Ammodendron</p>
         </div>
